  "text": "The Kubernetes API Server authentication chain is implemented across multiple Go source files in kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0. The primary chain construction occurs in pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go, specifically in the Config.New() method (lines 100-235), which orchestrates the assembly of multiple authenticator layers.\n\n**Chain Construction Flow:**\n\nThe authenticator chain is built in this order within Config.New():\n\n1. **Request Header Authenticator** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/headerrequest/requestheader.go) - Front-proxy authentication for externally authenticated requests\n\n2. **X509 Certificate Authenticator** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/x509/x509.go) - Client certificate mutual TLS authentication using NewDynamic() which validates client certificates against a CA bundle\n\n3. **Bearer Token Authenticators** - Combined via a token union (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/union/union.go):\n   - Token file authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/tokenfile/tokenfile.go) via newAuthenticatorFromTokenFile()\n   - Legacy service account authenticator (pkg/serviceaccount/legacy.go) via newLegacyServiceAccountAuthenticator() which uses pkg/serviceaccount/jwt.go\n   - Modern service account JWT authenticator (pkg/serviceaccount/jwt.go::JWTTokenAuthenticator) via newServiceAccountAuthenticator()\n   - Bootstrap token authenticator (plugin/pkg/auth/authenticator/token/bootstrap/bootstrap.go)\n   - JWT authenticators from AuthenticationConfiguration (OIDC support)\n   - Webhook token authenticator\n   - All token authenticators are wrapped in optional caching layer (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/cache/cached_token_authenticator.go)\n\n4. **Bearer Token Request Handler** - The token union is wrapped in a bearer token request authenticator (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/bearertoken/bearertoken.go) which extracts bearer tokens from Authorization headers and passes them to the token authenticator chain\n\n5. **WebSocket Protocol Authenticator** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/websocket/protocol.go) - Handles bearer token authentication for WebSocket connections\n\n6. **Request Union** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/union/union.go) - All request authenticators (header, x509, bearer token, websocket) are combined via union.New()\n\n7. **Group Adder** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/group/authenticated_group_adder.go) - The union authenticator is wrapped to automatically add system:authenticated group for non-anonymous, authenticated users\n\n8. **Anonymous Authenticator** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/anonymous/anonymous.go) - If enabled, anonymous authentication is wrapped using union.NewFailOnError(), which means authentication failures from previous authenticators will not prevent anonymous authentication fallback\n\n**Core Components:**\n\n- **Authenticator Interfaces** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/authenticator/interfaces.go):\n  - Token interface: AuthenticateToken(ctx, token) for token-based authentication\n  - Request interface: AuthenticateRequest(req *http.Request) for request-based authentication\n  - Response struct contains authenticated User and Audiences\n\n- **Service Account Token Authentication** (pkg/serviceaccount/jwt.go):\n  - JWTTokenAuthenticator() function creates a generic JWT token authenticator parameterized by private claims type\n  - PublicKeysGetter interface provides public keys for signature verification\n  - Validator interface allows domain-specific validation logic\n  - StaticPublicKeysGetter creates a static key provider\n\n- **Legacy Service Account Support** (pkg/serviceaccount/legacy.go):\n  - NewLegacyValidator() creates validators for service account tokens stored in secrets\n  - Supports optional lookups to verify token hasn't been invalidated\n  - LegacyIssuer constant identifies legacy service account tokens\n\n**Key Functions in Chain Construction:**\n\n- Config.New() (pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go:100) - Main orchestrator\n- newAuthenticatorFromTokenFile() - Creates token file authenticator\n- newLegacyServiceAccountAuthenticator() - Creates legacy service account token authenticator\n- newServiceAccountAuthenticator() - Creates modern JWT-based service account authenticator\n- newJWTAuthenticator() - Creates OIDC/JWT authenticators from AuthenticationConfiguration\n- newWebhookTokenAuthenticator() - Creates webhook token authenticator"
